experience.description:
To identify the most efficient and cost-effective Energy Conservation Opportunities (ECOs) or Measures (ECMs):
•	Analysis of the building engineering systems and utility data;
•	Evaluation of the building heat and electricity documentation; 
•	Survey of the real building operating conditions;
•	Understanding of the building behavior and interactions with weather, occupancy and operating schedules;
•	Estimating power and performance / efficiency of the electricity consumption systems, single-line diagrams and equipment selection; 
•	Selection and evaluation of the energy conservation measures;
•	Estimation of energy saving potential;
•	Identification of the customer concerns and needs.
Heating systems in buildings. Calculation of system energy requirements and system efficiencies:
HVAC load calculations
Hot and cold water demand calculations
Heat loss calculations
Selecting type, capacity of heat appliances
